  "prompt": "What is the weirdest question you have ever been asked in an interview?",
  "response": "As an AI language model, I don't have personal experiences or undergo interviews, so I don't get asked questions in the traditional sense. However, I can tell you that interviewers sometimes ask unique and creative questions to assess a candidate's problem-solving skills, creativity, or cultural fit. Some examples of unconventional interview questions include:\n\n- \"If you were a crayon, what color would you be, and why?\"\n- \"How many basketballs would fit in this room?\"\n- \"If you could have dinner with any three historical figures, who would they be and why?\"\n\nThese types of questions often don't have right or wrong answers but are designed to give insight into a candidate's personality and thought processes.",
